tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE women_in_leadership (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    industry VARCHAR(50),
    position VARCHAR(50),
    company VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE women_leaders (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    industry VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    position VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    company VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE leadership_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    leader_id INT NOT NULL,
    analysis_date DATE NOT NULL,
    analysis_result VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT fk_leader_id FOREIGN KEY (leader_id) REFERENCES women_leaders(id)
);

CREATE TABLE women_leaders (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR,
    industry VARCHAR,
    position VARCHAR,
    age INT,
    experience_years INT
);

CREATE TABLE leader_statistics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    leader_id INT,
    industry VARCHAR,
    position VARCHAR,
    years_in_position INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (leader_id) REFERENCES women_leaders(id)
);

CREATE TABLE WomenLeaders (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    industry VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    position VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    years_in_role INT,
    contact_email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);

CREATE TABLE LeadershipExperience (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    leader_id INT REFERENCES WomenLeaders(id),
    company_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE women_in_leadership (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  industry VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  role VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  leadership_experience_years INT
)

CREATE TABLE leadership_experience (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  leader_id INT NOT NULL,
  experience_start_date DATE,
  experience_end_date DATE,
  organization VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE leadership_skills (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  leader_id INT NOT NULL,
  skill_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  skill_level VARCHAR(20)
)

CREATE TABLE leadership_recognition (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  leader_id INT NOT NULL,
  recognition_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  recognition_year INT
)

CREATE TABLE leadership_institution (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  institution_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  leader_id INT
)
